        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500"> Chinese Hedge Fund Buys the Dip in Tech Stocks</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">A top-performing Chinese hedge fund, Huaan Hexin, is <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/international/2024/10/11/hedge-fund-up-800-in-seven-years-buys-dip-in-china-tech-stocks/" target="_blank">seizing</a> the opportunity to buy the dip in Chinese tech stocks after a recent slump in the Hang Seng Tech Index. Founder Yuan Wei believes that despite the market volatility, these stocks are undervalued compared to their fundamentals. The firm’s flagship fund has already surged 60% this year, driven by the government’s economic stimulus and a strong rally in internet stocks. Yuan remains bullish on companies like Alibaba and Tencent, viewing them as safe bets with strong profit potential, even amid China’s economic challenges.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
