        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500"> Hedge Funds Cut Bearish Brent Bets Amid War Tensions </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-oct-15-2.jpg" alt="Hedge Funds Cut Bearish Brent Bets Amid War Tensions" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Hedge funds are <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/10/11/hedge-funds-dump-bets-against-brent-at-fastest-pace-in-8-years/" target="_blank">slashing</a> bearish bets on Brent crude oil at the fastest pace in nearly eight years. With rising geopolitical tensions in the Middle East, particularly concerns about potential retaliation against Iran, investors are steering clear of betting against rising oil prices. Bullish positions on Brent and WTI oil have surged, with speculators also increasing bets on gasoline prices. As the markets brace for further developments, hedge funds are betting on oil remaining strong in the short term, reflecting the global uncertainty in energy markets.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
